<section id="To_create_a_Role" remap="TID_15017">
	<title>Creating a Role</title>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Create a Role</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Configure</guimenu><guisubmenu>Configuration</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click on the <guilabel>Access Control</guilabel> accordion, then click <guilabel>Roles</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Configuration</guilabel>), and 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/plus_green.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject>(<guilabel>Add a new Role</guilabel>).
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				In the <guilabel>Role Information</guilabel> area, type a name for the new role. For <guilabel>VM &amp; Template Access Restriction</guilabel>, select if you want to limit users with this role to only see virtual machines specifically used by the user, by the user or its group, or all virtual machines.
			</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/2095.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Under <guilabel>Product Features (Editing)</guilabel>, navigate to the appropriate feature and enable or disable it.
			</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/2096.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Add</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>
